import React from 'react'
import { Container, Row, Col, Image } from 'react-bootstrap';
import img1 from '../assets/grid1.jpg'
import img2 from '../assets/grid2.jpg'
import img3 from '../assets/grid3.jpg'
import img4 from '../assets/grid4.jpg'

const MainGrid = () => {
  return (
    <Container className="mt-4">
      {/* First Row with two columns */}
      <Row>
        <Col md={6}>
          <Image src={img1} alt="Steve Madden" fluid className="custom-image" />
        </Col>
        <Col md={6} className="d-flex flex-column">
          <Row>
            <Col>
              <Image src={img2} alt="Superdry" fluid className="custom-image mb-3" />
            </Col>
          </Row>
          <Row>
            <Col>
              <Image src={img3} alt="Guess" fluid className="custom-image" />
            </Col>
          </Row>
        </Col>
      </Row>
      {/* Second Row with one column taking full width */}
      <Row className="mt-3">
        <Col>
          <Image src={img4} alt="Tommy Hilfiger" fluid className="custom-image" />
        </Col>
      </Row>
    </Container>
  )
}

export default MainGrid
